annotationA: Importin subunit beta; Required for nuclear protein import and mediates docking of import substrate to distinct nucleoporins. In Drosophila, may not function as a snRNP import receptor as it does not interact with components of the snRNP complex such as snRNP U1, U2, U4/U6 and Snup
annotationB: Nuclear transport factor-2 (Ntf-2) is an essential gene regulating nuclear import. Ntf-2 binds to the nuclear pore protein DCTN4-p62 and to Ran and regulates the nuclear import of nuclear localization signal containing proteins
